olive oil
3 potato
1 packet chicken breast
1 packet mayonnaise
1 packet fine breadcrumbs
1 stalk celery
1 bag slaw mix
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Smokey Aioli
1 sachet Louisiana spice blend

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut potato into bite-sized chunks.
• SPICY! This is a mild spice blend, but use less if you're sensitive to heat! Place
potato on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, sprinkle with Louisiana
spice blend and season with salt. Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then roast
until tender, 20-25 minutes.

Little cooks: Kids can help with sprinkle over the spices and toss the potato.

• Meanwhile, slice chicken breast into 2cm strips. In a medium bowl, combine
chicken and mayonnaise. Season with salt and pepper.
• In a shallow bowl, add fine breadcrumbs and season. Coat handfuls of
chicken in the breadcrumbs. Transfer to a plate.
• Heat a large frying pan over high heat with a generous drizzle of olive oil.
When oil is hot, cook crumbed chicken until golden, 2 minutes each side.

TIP: The chicken will finish cooking in step 3!

Little cooks: Kids can help crumb the chicken! Use one hand for the wet
ingredients and the other for the dry ingredients so you don't end up with sticky
fingers. Make sure to wash your hands afterwards.

• Transfer chicken to a second lined oven tray, then bake until cooked
through, 8-10 minutes.
• Meanwhile, thinly slice celery. In a second medium bowl, combine slaw
mix, celery, baby spinach leaves and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and
olive oil. Season to taste.

Little cooks: Take the lead by combining the ingredients for the salad!

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it is no longer pink inside.

• Divide Louisiana potatoes and mayo-crumbed chicken between plates.
• Serve with slaw and smokey aioli. Enjoy!